This paper deals with quantum interactive proof systems, which are a topic of interest in both quantum computing (cs.QC) and computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of short messages is a key aspect of the paper, which could also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves analyzing the expressive power of a class of quantum interactive proof systems, which could be seen as a problem in data structures (cs.DS) or machine learning (cs.LG).
